On June 22, 2016, the President signed into law several bills. H.R. 812, known as the "Indian Trust Asset Reform Act," makes revisions to the management of Indian trust assets by the Department of the Interior. H.R. 1762 designates the Department of Veterans Affairs community-based outpatient clinic in The Dalles, Oregon, as the Loren R. Kaufman VA Clinic. H.R. 2137, titled the "Federal Law Enforcement Self-Defense and Protection Act of 2015," allows certain Federal law enforcement officers to continue carrying government-issued firearms even during times of involuntary furloughs. H.R. 2212 transfers Federal land in Lassen County, California, into trust status for the benefit of the Susanville Indian Rancheria. Lastly, S. 2276, known as the "Protecting our Infrastructure of Pipelines and Enhancing Safety Act of 2016," reauthorizes various programs of the Transportation Department's Pipeline and Hazardous Materials Safety Administration, sets minimum safety standards for underground natural gas storage facilities, and authorizes the issuance of emergency orders to impose restrictions on gas or hazardous liquid pipeline facilities.